data.enText: any of the tubes that carry blood from the heart to other parts of the body

data.chText: 干线（指主要公路、河流、铁路线等）
data.enText: a large and important road, river, railway/railroad line, etc.

simple_means.memory_skill: arter 管道 + y 表性质 → 动脉

means: 干线(指主要公路、河流、铁路线等)

tr: a major thoroughfare that bears important traffic
a blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the body

value.def: Arteries are the tubes in your body that carry blood from your heart to the rest of your body.
You can refer to an important main route within a complex road, railway, or river system as an artery .

example.ex: Clarence Street was one of the northbound arteries of the central business district.
example.tran: 克拉伦斯街是中央商业区北段部分的主干路之一。

example.ex: ...the point where the Ohio River, itself a great artery, joins the Mississippi.
example.tran: 本身就是一条主干河道的俄亥俄河和密西西比河的交汇处

partsOfSpeech.dec: arter 管道 + ial 具有…的 → 人体中）具有管道性质的 → 动脉的
arterio〔= arter〕管道 + tom 切割 + y 表名词 → 动脉切开术，动脉解剖学
partsOfSpeech.d: 动脉切开术，动脉解剖学

partsOfSpeech.dec: arter 管道 + itis 表炎症 → 动脉炎
arter 管道 + y 表性质 → 动脉
